tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE pharmaceutical_distribution (
	id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
	product_name TEXT,
	manufacturer TEXT,
	quantity INT,
	location TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE ProcessImprovements (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    bottleneck_id INT,
    improvement_description TEXT,
    implemented_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (bottleneck_id) REFERENCES Bottlenecks(id)
);

CREATE TABLE PharmaceuticalDistribution (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name VARCHAR(255),
    distributor VARCHAR(255),
    distribution_center VARCHAR(255),
    quantity INT,
    shipment_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE BottleneckIdentification (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  bottleneck_name VARCHAR(255),
  analysis_date DATE,
  identified_cause TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE ProcessImprovements (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  improvement_name VARCHAR(255),
  implementation_date DATE,
  impact_metrics TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE PharmaceuticalDistribution (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  product_name VARCHAR(255),
  quantity_in_stock INT,
  expiration_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE SupplyChainEfficiency (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  efficiency_metrics TEXT,
  improvement_strategy TEXT,
  implementation_date DATE
)
